19/10/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn confirmed on Tuesday (18 October) that Stabilisation and Association Agreement negotiations with BiH could start by the end of this year. 
Rehn's statement came as the BiH House of Peoples adopted an agreement on police reform, a key precondition for the talks.
Meeting in Brussels Tuesday with BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic, EU Justice and Home Affairs Commissioner Franco Frattini praised BiH's progress. 
During his visit, Terzic also held talks with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer, who reiterated that BiH must co-operate fully with the UN war crimes tribunal and meet technical prerequisites for NATO membership before it can join the Alliance.
In other news, the city of Mostar kicked off a two-day meeting on co-operation in processing of war crimes cases Wednesday. 
Experts from BiH, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro are participating. 
(Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 19/10/05; Fena, RTRS, NTV Hayat, OHR Sources - 18/10/05)
